---
import { faqs, processSteps } from '../lib/content';
import { canonicalContactUrl } from '../lib/site';
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-grid">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Queensland-based vehicle transport</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Take the car. Take the essentials. Keep the move simpler.</h1>
      <p class="hero-intro">
        Car Transport With Personal Items is built for interstate moves where approved belongings can stay inside the car,
        the route is checked properly, and the booking makes sense before pickup day arrives.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href={canonicalContactUrl}>Request A Route Review</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="/services/">See How The Service Works</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-notes">
        <div class="hero-note">
          <strong>Declared upfront</strong>
          <span>The route, vehicle, and approved contents are reviewed together instead of being treated like a standard car-only move.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-note">
          <strong>Built for real relocations</strong>
          <span>Useful when you need a few essentials to travel with the vehicle and want to avoid splitting everything into separate freight jobs.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-note">
          <strong>Practical next step</strong>
          <span>The quote process asks for the details that actually affect approval, timing, and pricing so the answer is more useful from the start.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-visual">
      <div class="visual-card">
        <img
          src="/brand-test-hero.svg"
          alt="Loaded car travelling across a warm desert highway illustration."
          width="1200"
          height="900"
        />
        <div class="route-pill">
          <strong>Brand position</strong>
          <span>Practical interstate car transport for customers who want approved belongings left inside and a cleaner moving day.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="visual-meta">
          <strong>Why it stands out</strong>
          <span>Warm highway tones, stronger typography, and a transport-first story instead of another anonymous service template.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="proof-strip">
  <div class="proof-frame">
    <div class="proof-item">
      <strong>Route fit first</strong>
      <p>We start with the route, the vehicle, and the approved contents because that is what decides whether the booking is viable.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="proof-item">
      <strong>Fewer moving parts</strong>
      <p>The service suits people who want the car and a few essentials moved together instead of juggling a separate freight booking as well.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="proof-item">
      <strong>Clear next step</strong>
      <p>The goal is not to impress you with filler. It is to make it obvious what to send so the team can give you a useful answer quickly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="section-kicker">Why customers use this service</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Built for moves where the car and the essentials need to stay together.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="section-intro">
        This is for customers who want a practical interstate move, not extra organising. The service works best when the route, the car, and the approved items are treated as one job from the start.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="difference-grid">
      <article class="difference-block">
        <h3>Keep a few essentials with the vehicle</h3>
        <p>That can mean fewer bookings to coordinate and fewer decisions to chase while you are already planning an interstate move.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="difference-block">
        <h3>Know where the booking stands before pickup</h3>
        <p>Declared contents, carrier approval, and route fit are checked early so customers are not left making assumptions the week the vehicle is due to move.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="difference-block">
        <h3>Get a more grounded answer</h3>
        <p>The quote is based on the real job details, which makes the pricing guidance and the preparation advice far more useful.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="process-band">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="section-kicker">Booking logic</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The proof is in how the booking is handled.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="section-intro">
        This service is more credible when the page is honest about approvals, declared items, and handover paperwork. Those details are the trust signals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="step-grid">
      {processSteps.map((step, index) => (
        <article class="step-card">
          <span>{index + 1}</span>
          <h3>{step.title}</h3>
          <p>{step.description}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="section-kicker">Common questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The details matter, so the answers should too.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="section-intro">
        These are the practical questions customers ask when they are trying to work out whether this booking style fits their move and what they should prepare before asking for a quote.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <article class="faq-card">
          <h3>{faq.question}</h3>
          <p>{faq.answer}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="cta-panel">
      <div class="cta-inner">
        <div class="cta-copy">
          <h2>Start with the route and the contents, not guesswork.</h2>
          <p>
            Send the origin, destination, vehicle details, and the approved items you want left inside. The team can then confirm fit, restrictions,
            likely handling requirements, and the most useful next step.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a class="button button-primary" href={canonicalContactUrl}>Talk To The Team</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
